article.headline: Dayton 79, North Carolina A&T 66
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Brian Roberts scored 30 points and pulled in seven rebounds to lead Dayton to a 79-66 victory over North Carolina A&T on Wednesday night. Dayton (2-0) shot just 38 percent in the first half, falling behind 35-29 at halftime. The Flyers bounced back in the second half, getting 19 points from Roberts and shooting 54 percent as a team. Scott Monty scored 16 points for the Flyers, and Charles Little chipped in with 11. Steven Rush led the Aggies (0-4) with 17 points and Austin Ewing added 16. Center Jason Wills scored 16, but Dayton still managed to outscore North Carolina A&T 44-16 in the paint. Roberts, who also scored 29 in Dayton's season opener against Austin Peay, went 11-of-20 from the field, and made 4-of-10 3-pointers.
